ackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wqy1665702521491.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wqy1665702521491.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wqy1665702521491.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wqy1665702521491\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__rocket_uniface_library_localvars_releaseshort__4\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This is the Uniface Library, the complete documentation for <span class=\"ph\">Rocket® Uniface</span>, the most productive environment for building enterprise\n      web, mobile, and desktop applications. Uniface also enables you to integrate multiple\n      databases, technologies, and operating platforms. </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__note_w1465ab1b5b3_w1466ab1b5_w1467ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Uniface is available in two\n         editions—the Community Edition and the Enterprise Edition. This documentation covers both\n         editions, so information that is applicable only to the Community Edition is clearly\n         indicated. For information on the differences, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uoz1665702521740.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uoz1665702521740.html\" title=\"Rocket Uniface is an environment for developing, integrating, deploying, and managing enterprise applications that run on a wide range of platforms and databases, and integrate with many other technologies.\">About Rocket Uniface</a>.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__topic_d12e1_d13e1_d14e1_d15e1_d16e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d423300e72\">What's New in Uniface 10 (<span class=\"ph\">10.4.03.041</span>) </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xhh1730183785459.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xhh1730183785459.html\" title=\"The Uniface 10 documentation is regularly updated to reflect new features, enhancements, bug fixes, and user feedback.\">What's New in the Documentation for this Patch (10.4.03.041)</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d2e1_d3e1_d4e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zll1665702760847.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zll1665702760847.html\" title=\"The Uniface 10 documentation is regularly updated to reflect new features, enhancements, bug fixes, and user feedback.\">What's New in Uniface 10.4.03</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d8e1_d9e1_d10e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qsp1665702762069.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsp1665702762069.html\" title=\"Uniface 10 features the Uniface IDE, a powerful new development environment for developing Uniface applications.\">What's New in Uniface 10 Compared to Uniface 9</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"emw1665702761424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/emw1665702761424.html\" title=\"Rocket® Uniface 10.4.02 introduces the ability to throw and catch exceptions to handle ProcScript and user-defined errors. It also opens up the USYSHTTP component so that you can customize its behavior when processing web requests from the Web Request Dispatcher (WRD).\">What's New in Uniface 10.4.02</a></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__topic_d17e1_d18e1_d19e1_d20e1_d21e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d423300e126\">\n Content Overview\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__p_d2e1_d3e1_d4e1\">The following topics provide an overview of information about Uniface and how to use it.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__table_d2e1_d3e1_d4e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           About Uniface 10 \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d20e1_d21e1_d22e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uoz1665702521740.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uoz1665702521740.html\" title=\"Rocket Uniface is an environment for developing, integrating, deploying, and managing enterprise applications that run on a wide range of platforms and databases, and integrate with many other technologies.\">About Rocket Uniface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d23e1_d24e1_d25e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bdt1692183880956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bdt1692183880956.html\" title=\"The Uniface IDE is an integrated collection of tools for building and integrating the components and libraries required for Uniface web, desktop, and mobile applications. Application definitions that are created with the Uniface IDE are stored in the Repository, an SQL-enabled database.\">Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d26e1_d27e1_d28e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qsp1665702762069.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsp1665702762069.html\" title=\"Uniface 10 features the Uniface IDE, a powerful new development environment for developing Uniface applications.\">What's New in Uniface 10 Compared to Uniface 9</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Getting Started \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d29e1_d30e1_d31e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"etd1665702764995.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etd1665702764995.html\" title=\"In addition to the documentation, you can find many other resources to help you use Uniface effectively.\">Learning Resources</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d32e1_d33e1_d34e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gkr1665702760703.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gkr1665702760703.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to create development objects, and then build them into Uniface archive files that are immediately deployed into a standalone test environment.\">Developing Applications with Uniface</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n                        Installing Uniface \n                        <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d35e1_d36e1_d37e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kju1665702765073.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kju1665702765073.html\" title=\"To install Uniface on Microsoft Windows, run the installer and respond to the prompts as required. You can then configure Uniface to work with your preferred databases and web servers.\">Installing and Configuring Uniface on Microsoft Windows</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d38e1_d39e1_d40e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qhg1665702746675.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhg1665702746675.html\" title=\"To install Uniface on Unix and Linux platforms run the installation program. After installation, you can configure Uniface to work with your preferred databases and web servers.\">Installing and Configuring Uniface on Unix and Linux Platforms</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d41e1_d42e1_d43e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zor1720422284512.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zor1720422284512.html\" title=\"To install Uniface on iSeries, you need to extract the electronic distribution (e-dist) onto an IFS share. The e-dist is a self-extracting executable that runs on Windows and contains the installation program and all other files needed to install Uniface.\">Installing and Configuring Uniface on iSeries</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n                        Uniface License Management \n                        <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d44e1_d45e1_d46e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nzw1665702745583.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nzw1665702745583.html\" title=\"Uniface makes use of Sentinel to handle licensing of Uniface products.\">Uniface License Management</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d47e1_d48e1_d49e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxq1665702745800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxq1665702745800.html\" title=\"We offer a number of Sentinel license types for Uniface. When registering with Uniface, you are given an Entitlement Certificate that defines the license model, deployment type, as well as the conditions and permissions associated with the license.\">Sentinel License Types</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d50e1_d51e1_d52e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdm1665702750049.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdm1665702750049.html\">Troubleshooting Licensing Issues</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" rowspan=\"3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Developing Applications \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d53e1_d54e1_d55e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tvp1692183875183.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tvp1692183875183.html\" title=\"Uniface application development is model-driven and component-based. When developing Uniface applications, you first model the application data and behavior as modeled objects, before constructing components based on the model.\">Uniface Development Paradigm</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d56e1_d57e1_d58e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ffi1703160534674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffi1703160534674.html\" title=\"Modeling is an activity in which you create abstract development objects that can be reused by other objects during development. Modeled objects are used to represent the application data, centralize business logic, define default behavior, and enforce consistency.\">Modeling the Application</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d59e1_d60e1_d61e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrw1665702750469.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrw1665702750469.html\" title=\"During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase.\">Constructing Components and Other Objects</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d62e1_d63e1_d64e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ery1665702625513.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ery1665702625513.html\" title=\"When Uniface development objects are compiled, the compiler checks the definition, syntax, and integrity of the object, inserts inherited ProcScript modules, resolves IncludeScript references and constant definitions, compiles the resulting code, and generates compiled runtime objects and descriptors. It can optionally generate files that show an object's ProcScript after inherited and included ProcScript has been resolved.\">Compilation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d65e1_d66e1_d67e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkg1665702765370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkg1665702765370.html\" title=\"Uniface provides tools and ProcScript instructions to help you debug applications during development, and to monitor and control the execution of ProcScript in a running application.\">Debugging Uniface Applications</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Developing Web Applications \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d68e1_d69e1_d70e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nvu1665702750539.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvu1665702750539.html\" title=\"You can use Uniface to develop, test, and deploy web-based applications. Web applications have unique requirements with regard to testing and deployment, state management and authentication, data maintenance, and security.\">Developing Web Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d71e1_d72e1_d73e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jix1665702767902.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jix1665702767902.html\" title=\"When developing a web application you need to follow the Uniface development paradigm of model, construct, build, test, and deploy. Web applications are stateless, so you need to consider how you will manage state, how to maximize performance, and protect security.\">Develop a Uniface Web Application</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d74e1_d75e1_d76e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"axe1665702642391.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/axe1665702642391.html\" title=\"Web applications present developers with more security challenges than a desktop or client/server application. Application and network security can no longer be treated as separate realms, and web applications are responsible for maintaining user state and addressing the many security threats that arise out of the open nature of the web.\">Web Security Guidelines</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Developing Desktop Applications \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d77e1_d78e1_d79e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"shh1665702750613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/shh1665702750613.html\" title=\"Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications.\">Developing Desktop Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d80e1_d81e1_d82e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"igi1665702750681.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/igi1665702750681.html\" title=\"When developing a desktop application you follow the normal Uniface development paradigm of model, construct, compile, and test.\">Developing a Uniface Desktop Application</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d83e1_d84e1_d85e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxt1665702612061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxt1665702612061.html\" title=\"Forms are presentation components used in desktop applications and reports are used for printing. They are created in the same way.\">Constructing Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d86e1_d87e1_d88e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jpo1705564833726.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jpo1705564833726.html\" title=\"Runtime libraries contain objects that can be used by all components in the application. These objects can include global objects, such as messages, menus, and global variables, as well as translation tables and language setups.\">Libraries of Runtime Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Developing Mobile Apps \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d89e1_d90e1_d91e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"evi1665702676990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evi1665702676990.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to develop cross-platform mobile apps using dynamic server pages (DSPs), JavaScript APIs to access device functionality, and a third-party hybrid framework to package the app for Android and iOS devices. This makes it possible to develop the same code for all platforms, but take advantage of native functionality.\">Developing Mobile Apps</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d92e1_d93e1_d94e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"unv1665702768403.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unv1665702768403.html\" title=\"Uniface's mobile solution is based on web technologies, so mobile development starts with creating a responsive web application that is tailored to the possibilities and limitations of mobile devices.\">Developing a Mobile App</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Scripting \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d95e1_d96e1_d97e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvf1665702667063.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvf1665702667063.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications.\">Scripting Application Behavior</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d98e1_d99e1_d100e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"caq1665702624398.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/caq1665702624398.html\" title=\"Code containers are properties of components, application shells, entities and fields that hold the ProcScript and JavaScript code used to define application behavior for the specific object.\">Code Containers</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d101e1_d102e1_d103e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtm1665702624482.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" title=\"A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.\">Script Modules</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d104e1_d105e1_d106e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jcx1707814817129.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jcx1707814817129.html\" title=\"ProcScript provides high-level statements, functions, expressions, and operators that enable you to efficiently manipulate data and script application behavior. It is a powerful language that condenses complex processing into single commands.\">ProcScript Syntax</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lem1707814690530.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lem1707814690530.html\" title=\"JavaScript is a widely-used scripting language used to extend HTML with dynamic behavior. Uniface supports the use of JavaScript to implement script modules in Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs), and provides an API for addressing Uniface data objects.\">JavaScript</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kec1718082865771.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kec1718082865771.html\" title=\"A Struct is a tree-like data structure in memory that is used to dynamically manipulate complex data and transform it from or to XML, JSON, or Uniface component data. A Struct can be addressed by assigning it to a variable, parameter, or non-database field of type struct, and manipulated using ProcScript commands, access operators, and information functions. For information on using Structs, see Transforming Complex Data Using Structs.\">Structs</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Testing and Debugging \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxt1665702750826.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxt1665702750826.html\" title=\"Uniface includes a pre-configured test environment that you can use for unit testing, and a Debugger to analyze problems.\">Testing and Debugging</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d116e1_d117e1_d118e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qhw1665702765447.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhw1665702765447.html\" title=\"The Uniface Debugger is a Uniface application that can connect to a local or remote Uniface application process so that you can conduct step-by-step, real time analysis of the executing ProcScript. It enables you to find and correct ProcScript errors, investigate application behavior, and improve code in all types of Uniface application.\">Uniface Debugger</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Running Applications \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d119e1_d120e1_d121e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"une1692169858701.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/une1692169858701.html\" title=\"The Uniface runtime paradigm rests on three major pillars: Multi-platform Operation, Connectivity, and Technology Integration. In fact, Uniface can be used almost purely as an integration platform.\">Uniface Runtime Paradigm</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d122e1_d123e1_d124e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hzq1692173422967.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hzq1692173422967.html\" title=\"The Uniface runtime environment includes executables, servers, and drivers that enable Uniface to run on almost all platforms and deployment environments. It also includes tools for deploying Uniface applications into the runtime environment.\">Uniface Runtime Environment</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d125e1_d126e1_d127e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sha1665702562347.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sha1665702562347.html\" title=\"Uniface enables applications to connect to a wide variety of data sources, including relational databases, files, or directory servers. For example, an application could connect to an Oracle database, files on a server, and an LDAP server. Database connectors provide the interface between Uniface and specific databases\">DBMS Support</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d128e1_d129e1_d130e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rhw1665702768776.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rhw1665702768776.html\" title=\"The Uniface IDE is a Windows application, but the Uniface applications you build with it can run on many operating systems and platforms. Uniface provides built-in mechanisms for handling input and output on all these platforms.\">Platform Support</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d131e1_d132e1_d133e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fus1665702745424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fus1665702745424.html\" title=\"The Uniface Universal Request Broker (URB) architecture allows you to deploy an application independently of architecture. It supports bidirectional, synchronous, and asynchronous communication between components. Components can access data in distributed databases and can be configured to run on any supported architecture.\">Universal Request Broker</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d134e1_d135e1_d136e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ofu1665702741888.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ofu1665702741888.html\" title=\"Deploying a Uniface application entails installing the Uniface runtime servers in the appropriate locations, distributing the application runtime objects to the most effective locations in the infrastructure, and editing the configuration files so that the Uniface runtime environment can locate the required resources.\">Deploying Applications</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Deployment and Configuration \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d137e1_d138e1_d139e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ofu1665702741888.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ofu1665702741888.html\" title=\"Deploying a Uniface application entails installing the Uniface runtime servers in the appropriate locations, distributing the application runtime objects to the most effective locations in the infrastructure, and editing the configuration files so that the Uniface runtime environment can locate the required resources.\">Deploying Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d140e1_d141e1_d142e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zhr1665702742172.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhr1665702742172.html\" title=\"Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly.\">Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           How Uniface Works \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d143e1_d144e1_d145e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bxr1665702598616.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bxr1665702598616.html\" title=\"Triggers can be activated by events originating from user actions, ProcScript statements, and external events (such as asynchronous interrupts).\">Trigger Activation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d146e1_d147e1_d148e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zge1665702663349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zge1665702663349.html\" title=\"Uniface allows you to access data in multiple DBMSs in a uniform way, simultaneously. The term DBMS is used generically here to describe any structured form of data storage that Uniface understands. According to this definition, a record management system is also a DBMS. All the actions carried out on database tables or files occur via the DBMS interface.\">Uniface Database I/O</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d149e1_d150e1_d151e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jtp1665702591408.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jtp1665702591408.html\" title=\"Uniface validates modified data to ensure that it is correct, meaning that it conforms to the declarative and procedural rules defined by the developer.\">Data Validation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d152e1_d153e1_d154e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xbb1665702769022.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xbb1665702769022.html\" title=\"Field interface definitions, as defined in the Database Interface property, determine how data is stored in a specific DBMS storage format, and how Uniface deals with the data when it is retrieved. The definitions specify the Uniface data type and packing code, which are mapped by the DBMS connector to the DBMS data type, known as a storage format.\">Data Storage</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d155e1_d156e1_d157e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"obl1692182341961.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/obl1692182341961.html\" title=\"Instances of Uniface components can communicate with each other synchronously or asynchronously, either locally (in the same process), or remotely (between different processes, which may be on different hosts).\">Component Communication</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d158e1_d159e1_d160e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ztx1665702751111.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ztx1665702751111.html\" title=\"The structure editor is the mechanism in Uniface that understands events in form components. The structure editor derives its name from the external data structure that exists when forms contain data.\">Structure Editor</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                           Integrating with Other Technologies \n                        </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d161e1_d162e1_d163e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"juz1692183224178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/juz1692183224178.html\" title=\"The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies.\">Integrating with Other Technologies</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d164e1_d165e1_d166e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zzx1665702678830.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" title=\"Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.\">Define a Component Signature</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d167e1_d168e1_d169e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lmy1665702545752.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lmy1665702545752.html\" title=\"A web service is software that makes its functionality available over the Internet.\">Web Services</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d170e1_d171e1_d172e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqm1665702769097.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqm1665702769097.html\" title=\"Uniface provides an API that makes it possible to integrate Uniface applications and programs created in 3GL programming languages such as C, C++, Visual Basic, Cobol, Fortran, and Pascal.\">C, C++, and Other 3GLs</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wqy1665702521491__li_d173e1_d174e1_d175e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nwm1665702769167.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nwm1665702769167.html\" title=\"To connect with COM components, Uniface makes use of the Microsoft's DCOM architecture. Uniface includes a COM connector that provides an interface with DCOM, thereby enabling Uniface components to call and be called by COM components.\">COM and DCOM</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3629601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3629601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Rocket Uniface Library 10.4 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 This is the Uniface Library, the complete documentation for Rocket® Uniface , the most productive environment for building enterprise web, mobile, and desktop applications. Uniface also enables you to integrate multiple databases, technologies, and operating platforms. Note: Uniface is available in two editions—the Community Edition and the Enterprise Edition. This documentation covers both editions, so information that is applicable only to the Community Edition is clearly indicated. For information on the differences, see About Rocket Uniface . What's New in Uniface 10 ( 10.4.03.041 ) What's New in the Documentation for this Patch (10.4.03.041) What's New in Uniface 10.4.03 What's New in Uniface 10 Compared to Uniface 9 What's New in Uniface 10.4.02 Content Overview The following topics provide an overview of information about Uniface and how to use it. About Uniface 10 About Rocket Uniface Uniface IDE What's New in Uniface 10 Compared to Uniface 9 Getting Started Learning Resources Developing Applications with Uniface Installing Uniface Installing and Configuring Uniface on Microsoft Windows Installing and Configuring Uniface on Unix and Linux Platforms Installing and Configuring Uniface on iSeries Uniface License Management Uniface License Management Sentinel License Types Troubleshooting Licensing Issues Developing Applications Uniface Development Paradigm Modeling the Application Constructing Components and Other Objects Compilation Debugging Uniface Applications Developing Web Applications Developing Web Applications Develop a Uniface Web Application Web Security Guidelines Developing Desktop Applications Developing Desktop Applications Developing a Uniface Desktop Application Constructing Forms and Reports Libraries of Runtime Objects Developing Mobile Apps Developing Mobile Apps Developing a Mobile App Scripting Scripting Application Behavior Code Containers Script Modules ProcScript Syntax JavaScript Structs Testing and Debugging Testing and Debugging Uniface Debugger Running Applications Uniface Runtime Paradigm Uniface Runtime Environment DBMS Support Platform Support Universal Request Broker Deploying Applications Deployment and Configuration Deploying Applications Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications How Uniface Works Trigger Activation Uniface Database I/O Data Validation Data Storage Component Communication Structure Editor Integrating with Other Technologies Integrating with Other Technologies Define a Component Signature Web Services C, C++, and Other 3GLs COM and DCOM Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}